    {
        "id": 66342,
        "title": "All-Out Attacks",
        "wikiUrl": "/wiki/All-Out_Attacks",
        "image": "AllOutAttacks-PTDN-EN-C-1E.png",
        "lore": "All monsters that are Special Summoned are changed to face-up Attack Position and must attack, if able, during the turn they are Special Summoned.",
        "archetypes": [
            "Summon Restriction"
        ],
        "actions": [
            "Changes Battle Positions"
        ],
        "effectTypes": [
            "Trigger-like"
        ],
        "imageUrl": "https://vignette1.wikia.nocookie.net/yugioh/images/5/5b/AllOutAttacks-PTDN-EN-C-1E.png",
        "tips": [
            {
                "value": " This card can be searched by \"A Cat of Ill Omen\" and \"The Despair Uranus\"."
            },
            {
                "value": " This card works well in an OTK strategy when used with \"Exodius the Ultimate Forbidden Lord\", \"Nimble Musasabi\" and \"Ojama Trio\"."
            },
            {
                "value": " This card can generate an instant OTK if used together with \"Ojama Trio\", making the Ojama Tokens attack a 2400+ ATK monster. A \"Chainsaw Insect\" is perhaps the best monster to overlap with this combo."
            },
            {
                "value": " Use \"All-Out Attacks\", \"Astral Barrier\", \"Des Counterblow\" and \"Damage Condenser\" to bring a powerful Level 5 or higher monster to the field."
            },
            {
                "value": " You can use this card in conjunction with \"Foolish Revival\". "
            },
            {
                "value": " Use \"An Unfortunate Report\" to force the opponent's monsters to attack yours twice."
            },
            {
                "value": " Use this card with any of the \"Yubel\" cards to inflict damage to your opponent's lifepoints."
            },
            {
                "value": " Combine this card with \"Raregold Armor\". \"All-Out Attacks\" may only be used as a decoy when your opponent attempts to Special Summon any monster"
            },
            {
                "value": " If you have no monsters you can use \"Rainbow Life\" or \"Confusion Chaff\""
            },
            {
                "value": " Use this card in a Deck in which \"Morphing Jar #2\" and \"Poison Mummy\" are the only monsters, for another OTK.",
                "subValues": [
                    {
                        "value": " Use the above mentioned combo with \"Hiro's Shadow Scout\" instead of \"Poison Mummy\" for a Mill OTK."
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "value": " If they attack a \"Volcanic Doomfire\" you can clear their field."
            },
            {
                "value": " Use this with \"Goyo Guardian\" to attack right away with the monsters that you steal with its effect after your Guardian destroys them in battle."
            },
            {
                "value": " This card can be used with numerous Plant monsters from Crossroads of Chaos which summon low-attack tokens on the opponents side of the field."
            },
            {
                "value": " Another strategy is to summon tokens on your opponent's turn by Special Summoning monsters while \"Black Garden\" is in play."
            },
            {
                "value": " If you Special Summon \"Grinder Golem\" or \"Volcanic Queen\", you force them to attack your stronger monsters to deal severe damage, specially if you do use Shrink or Burden of the Mighty. (In case you run a Grinder Golem do not forget to use Spirit Barrier or Hallowed Life Barrier to prevent damage by attacking with your Tokens)"
            },
            {
                "value": " This card works well in an OTK Strategy using \"Cactus Fighter\". On your opponents turn if this monster destroys another monster, using \"Shrink\", \"Rush Recklessly\", \"Fairy Box\", or any Quick-Play Spell card, or Trap Card which makes this monster stronger or the opposing monster weaker. The opponent's monster will be destroyed by this card and will summon a Token that will be forced to attack this monster, causing an infinite loop, resulting in a win by inflicting infinite life point damage.",
                "subValues": [
                    {
                        "value": "You can also force your opponent to into this situation by using cards such as \"Nightmare Archfiends\", \"Black Garden\" or combos using cards that summon tokens/monsters like \"Scapegoat\", \"Statue of the Wicked\" or \"Fires of Doomsday\" and cards that give control of your monsters to your opponent (and thus triggering the effect of \"All-Out Attacks\") like \"Creature Swap\", \"Shien's Spy\", \"Enemy Controller\" or \"Mystic Box\"."
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "value": " \"Stone Statue of the Aztecs\" and \"Sauropod Brachion\" reflect double battle damage when they are attacked. This card is perfect when the mentioned cards are the only monsters you have."
            },
            {
                "value": " You can use this card with \"Worm Zero\" to special summon Worm Victory and activate its flip effect, destroying all of the opponents face-up monsters."
            },
            {
                "value": " Combining this card with Cannon Soldier (or similar) and multiple copies of Spear Cretin can create an OTK loop."
            },
            {
                "value": " This card is good in Dark World Deck."
            },
            {
                "value": " Using this card can be a good defense against \"Superheavy Samurai\" monsters. Being they can attack in defense mode, and commonly have low attack points, \"All-Out Attacks\" can allow you to inflict damage to your opponent much more easily."
            }
        ],
        "sets": [
            {
                "number": "PTDN-EN075",
                "setName": "Phantom Darkness",
                "rarity": "Common"
            }
        ]
    },
