            {
                "value": " If you have a tuner on the field, and two \"Quillbolt Hedgehogs\" in the grave, plus \"Imperial Iron Wall\", you can do an infinite loop OTK that only requires one more card than the common Mass Driver based one."
            },
            {
                "value": " You can combine this with cards that can be summoned from the hand like \"Cyber Dragon\" and \"The Tricky\" to easily get the needed monsters on the field for this effect. Attacking with them as well could even allow for an OTK. This allows this card to be easily integrated into Tricky Turbo decks. Destiny HERO - Malicious can help this strategy."
            },
            {
                "value": " This is perfect for a Lightsworn deck because you can tribute the Special Summonable monsters in that deck such as \"Wulf, Lightsworn Beast\" and \"Judgment Dragon\". You can then bring them back to your hand with \"Beckoning Light\". \"Lumina, Lightsworn Summoner\" can aid in this as well."
            },
            {
                "value": " \"Amazoness Archer\" can Tribute herself as one of the two Monsters for her effect if all else fails, although this usually only the best option if doing so will deplete all of your opponent's Life Points."
            },
            {
                "value": " Use this card in a Hieratic/Red-Eyes deck to get the most out of this card's effect. Not only will the Hieratic's effects let you summon Normal Dragons in your possession, but you will be able to suggilate your opponent with burn damage repeatedly. "
            }
